headline: 3 Consumer Stocks Skating on Thin Ice
summary: The performance of consumer discretionary businesses is closely linked to economic cycles. This sensitive demand profile can lead to some stock price volatility, but over the past six months, the industry has stayed on track as its 6.3% return was close to the S&P 500’s.
